SciDB chunksize benchmark 600KB

Florian Lahn

24 März 2016

In this benchmarking test we used a small image file of 600KB and added it 300 times into a sequential spatial time series in SciDB. The purpose of this test is to test the time consumption on using the SciDB plugin for GDAL. The image used has size of 699x929 pixel and therefore the spatial chunksize 1000 covers the whole image, in order to test other chunksizes we also used 750 and 500 (quarter image resolution). The very first image upload marks the initialization of the time series, where no “insertInto” method is called. This value is assumed to have a smaller value than the rest of the data.
